Nice Saturday morning. This is what I did today ^_^
#TeaganAir
#TeaganAir
It's officially logged. I have 2.3 flight hours ^_^
If I had to describe what it's like to fly a small plane, I'd say it's like a mix of a motorcycle/quadracross and a boat at 4,000 feet in the air.
On the ground, you're immediately very fast. Everything is a bit unstable on the ground, hence motorcycle/quadracross.
And if you didn't know: You steer an airplane on the ground with your feet, not with the control yoke. Rudder pedals and brakes. It's no car.
In the air it is wobbly and one swims a little. It feels as if one is in a boat on water. One can steer it, but sometimes a wave comes and throws one off balance, so one has to get used to the sea motion, just in the air.
Just another random detail:
Flying is physically demanding. My back and my legs hurt today *as if* I had been at the fitness studio.
This is not like a Sunday outing with the car. It is more of a sport than a leisurely ride, in my newly acquired opinion.
A beautiful Saturday, my loves. Welcome at 4,000 feet.
I'm going up again tomorrow. Then we will practice streamer drop and slow flying.
The weather was turbulent today, but it was a lot of fun. We practiced slow flying and streamer drop. Once we had a ground speed of only 16 mph while flying at 65 mph.
It was a clear day up there, a bit overcast higher up, but still beautiful.
